You are an expert in TypeScript, Node.js, Next.js App Router, React, Shadcn UI, Radix UI, and Tailwind CSS.

# Project Type
This is a Next.js 14+ project using the App Router architecture with TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and Shadcn UI components.

## Code Style and Structure

- Write concise, technical TypeScript code with accurate examples
- Use functional and declarative programming patterns; avoid classes
- Prefer iteration and modularization over code duplication
- Use descriptive variable names with auxiliary verbs (e.g., isLoading, hasError, canSubmit)
- Structure files: exported component, subcomponents, helpers, static content, types
- Keep components small and focused — single responsibility principle
- Co-locate related files (component + its types + its styles)

## Naming Conventions

- Use lowercase with dashes for directories (e.g., components/auth-wizard)
- Use PascalCase for component files (e.g., AuthWizard.tsx)
- Use camelCase for utility files (e.g., formatDate.ts)
- Use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for constants (e.g., MAX_RETRY_COUNT)
- Favor named exports for components over default exports
- Prefix event handlers with "handle" (e.g., handleSubmit, handleClick)
- Prefix boolean state with "is", "has", "can", "should" (e.g., isOpen, hasError)

## TypeScript Usage

- Use TypeScript for all code; prefer interfaces over type aliases for object shapes
- Avoid enums; use const objects or string literal unions instead
- Use generic types to avoid code duplication
- Leverage TypeScript's discriminated unions for complex state
- Always type function parameters and return values explicitly
- Use `satisfies` operator to validate types without losing specificity
- Prefer `unknown` over `any`; use type guards to narrow types

## Next.js App Router Patterns

- Use Server Components by default; add "use client" only when necessary
- Implement proper loading states with loading.tsx files
- Use error.tsx for error boundaries at the route level
- Implement not-found.tsx for 404 handling
- Use route handlers (route.ts) for API endpoints
- Leverage generateMetadata() for dynamic SEO metadata
- Use generateStaticParams() for static generation of dynamic routes
- Implement proper caching with fetch() options and revalidate
- Use server actions for form submissions and mutations
- Organize routes in the (group) convention for logical grouping without URL impact

## File Organization

```
app/
  (auth)/
    login/page.tsx
    register/page.tsx
  (dashboard)/
    layout.tsx
    page.tsx
    settings/page.tsx
  api/
    users/route.ts
components/
  ui/              (shadcn generated)
  common/          (shared across pages)
  features/        (feature-specific)
lib/
  utils.ts
  validations/
  hooks/
  actions/         (server actions)
types/
  index.ts
  api.ts
```

## React and Component Patterns

- Use React Server Components (RSC) as the default
- Minimize `use client`, `useEffect`, and `useState`
- Use Zustand or React Context for client-side global state
- Implement Suspense boundaries for async data fetching
- Use `react-hook-form` with `zod` for form validation
- Wrap expensive computations with `useMemo` and `useCallback`
- Use `forwardRef` when passing refs to custom components
- Implement compound component pattern for complex UI

## Tailwind CSS Usage

- Use Tailwind utility classes exclusively; avoid custom CSS when possible
- Follow mobile-first responsive design (sm: md: lg: xl:)
- Use CSS variables for design tokens via Tailwind config
- Use `cn()` utility (clsx + tailwind-merge) for conditional classes
- Group related Tailwind classes logically (layout, spacing, color, typography)
- Extract repeated class combinations into component variants using CVA

## Shadcn UI and Radix UI

- Install components via `npx shadcn-ui@latest add [component]`
- Extend Shadcn components rather than modifying generated files
- Use Radix UI primitives for accessible, unstyled base components
- Always include proper aria labels and roles
- Implement keyboard navigation for interactive components

## Data Fetching

- Use React Query (TanStack Query) for client-side data fetching
- Implement optimistic updates for better UX
- Use SWR as alternative for simple cases
- Always handle loading, error, and empty states
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Cache server component fetches with appropriate strategies

## Error Handling Patterns

```typescript
// Server Action error handling
async function createUser(formData: FormData) {
  try {
    const validated = UserSchema.parse(Object.fromEntries(formData));
    await db.user.create({ data: validated });
    revalidatePath('/users');
    return { success: true };
  } catch (error) {
    if (error instanceof z.ZodError) {
      return { error: '输入数据验证失败', details: error.flatten() };
    }
    console.error('[createUser] 创建用户失败:', error);
    return { error: '服务器内部错误，请稍后重试' };
  }
}

// API Route error handling
export async function GET(request: Request) {
  try {
    const data = await fetchData();
    return Response.json(data);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('[GET /api/resource]:', error);
    return Response.json({ error: 'Internal Server Error' }, { status: 500 });
  }
}
```

## Performance Optimization

- Use `next/image` for all images with proper width/height
- Implement lazy loading with `next/dynamic` for heavy components
- Use `next/font` for font optimization
- Implement route prefetching strategically
- Use `Suspense` for granular loading states
- Analyze bundle with `@next/bundle-analyzer`
- Implement proper cache headers for static assets

## File Naming Conventions

- Pages: `page.tsx` (required by Next.js)
- Layouts: `layout.tsx`
- Loading states: `loading.tsx`
- Error boundaries: `error.tsx`
- Not found: `not-found.tsx`
- Server actions: `actions.ts` or `[feature].actions.ts`
- API routes: `route.ts`
- Components: `PascalCase.tsx`
- Utilities: `camelCase.ts`
- Types: `types.ts` or `[domain].types.ts`
- Hooks: `use[Name].ts`

## What Cursor Should Do

- Suggest App Router patterns over Pages Router
- Auto-import from correct paths (next/navigation over next/router)
- Generate Server Components by default, prompt "use client" only when needed
- Suggest `revalidatePath` or `revalidateTag` after mutations
- Recommend Zod schemas for all data validation
- Generate proper TypeScript types for API responses
- Suggest proper error handling with try/catch and user-friendly messages
- Recommend `next/image` whenever an `<img>` tag is used
- Generate accessible components with proper aria attributes
- Suggest parallel routes and intercepting routes for advanced layouts

## What Cursor Should Avoid

- Do NOT use `getServerSideProps` or `getStaticProps` (Pages Router patterns)
- Do NOT use `useRouter` from `next/router`; use `next/navigation` instead
- Do NOT use `class` components; use functional components only
- Do NOT use inline styles; use Tailwind classes
- Do NOT use `any` type; suggest proper typing
- Do NOT fetch data in Client Components when Server Components can do it
- Do NOT use `useEffect` for data fetching; use React Query or Server Components
- Do NOT hardcode API URLs; use environment variables
- Do NOT commit sensitive data or API keys
- Do NOT use deprecated Next.js APIs

## Environment Variables

- Prefix client-side vars with `NEXT_PUBLIC_`
- Keep server-side secrets without `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix
- Use `.env.local` for local development
- Document all required env vars in `.env.example`
- Validate env vars at startup using `zod` or `t3-env`

## Testing Conventions

- Write unit tests with Vitest or Jest
- Use React Testing Library for component tests
- Use Playwright or Cypress for E2E tests
- Mock server responses with MSW (Mock Service Worker)
- Test user interactions, not implementation details
- Aim for >80% coverage on business logic
